class="container--body-inner"><p>When I was growing up, Manwich, the canned sloppy joe sauce, was a family favorite for making and enjoying quick skillet meals. My still-speedy take uses gochujang for a smoky, spicy undertone. Treat this recipe as a way to hone your ideal levels of heat and sweetness by playing with the amount of gochujang, ketchup, and vinegar. Potato buns provide an ideal soft landing and cold pickle spears are a bright, crunchy counterpoint. When it comes to sloppy joes, the sloppier the better, so be sure to load up those buns and arm yourself with plenty of napkins! </p></div></div></div></div><div class="TextBlockWrapper-bNZsMC fMUEKc StyledTextblock-SJflO eYjtWF disclaimer"><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ TextBlockText-gtrMkY iUEiRd erbViy kQegaj">All products featured on Bon Appétit are independently selected by our editors. grid--item grid_content_columnOne"><div class="Wrapper-eWbbKr ifygAC" data-testid="IngredientList"><h2 class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Hed-kJkfJg iUEiRd dSSDuo koztfQ">Ingredients</h2><div class="List-iSNGTT guHkXK"><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. vegetable oil</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">lb. ground beef (ideally 20% fat)</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1½</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">tsp. Diamond Crystal or ¾ tsp. Morton kosher salt, divided, plus more</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl"></p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Freshly ground pepper</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">medium green bell pepper, ribs and seeds removed, chopped</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">medium onion, chopped</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">6&#8211;8</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">garlic cloves, finely grated</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">3</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. gochujang</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">2</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. ketchup</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. soy sauce</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. dark brown sugar</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">tsp. yellow mustard</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">15-oz. can tomato sauce</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">1</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Tbsp. balsamic vinegar</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl">4</p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">potato rolls</div><p class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Amount-hYcAMN iUEiRd gMBhLy hoAJEl"></p><div class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ Description-cSrMCf iUEiRd gMBhLy fsKnGI">Kosher dill spears and potato chips (for serving; optional)</div></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM eHLzLy grid--item grid_content_columnTwo"><div><div class="InstructionsWrapper-hZXqPx RmryN" data-testid="InstructionsWrapper"><h2 class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ InstructionListHed-dYZnS iUEiRd dSSDuo eeiAwJ">Preparation</h2><ol class="InstructionGroupWrapper-bqiIwp ccobUj"><li class="InstructionListWrapper-dcpygI jsIesN"><h4 class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ InstructionHed-cTDCYA InstructionHedSmall-kvDvLP iwCByY gDeIOw ssMUV">Step 1</h4><p>Heat <strong>1 Tbsp. vegetable oil</strong> in a large skillet over medium-high. Add <strong>1 lb. ground beef (ideally 20% fat)</strong>, spreading out in a single layer; sprinkle with <strong>1 tsp. Diamond Crystal or ½ tsp. Morton kosher salt</strong> and season with <strong>freshly ground pepper</strong>. Cook, undisturbed, until a light brown crust forms underneath, about 3 minutes. Continue to cook, breaking up with a wooden spoon, until almost completely brown all the way through, about 3 minutes more.</p><h4 class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ InstructionHed-cTDCYA InstructionHedSmall-kvDvLP iwCByY gDeIOw ssMUV">Step 2</h4><p>Push meat to one side of pan. Reduce heat to medium and add <strong>1 medium green bell pepper, ribs and seeds removed, chopped</strong>, <strong>1 medium onion, chopped</strong>, <strong>6–8 garlic cloves, finely grated</strong>, and <strong>½ tsp. Diamond Crystal or ¼ tsp. Morton kosher salt</strong>; season with pepper. Cook, stirring often, until vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in <strong>3 Tbsp. gochujang</strong>, <strong>2 Tbsp. ketchup</strong>, <strong>1 Tbsp. soy sauce</strong>, <strong>1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce</strong>, <strong>1 Tbsp. dark brown sugar</strong>, and <strong>1 tsp. yellow mustard</strong>, then add <strong>one 15-oz. can tomato sauce</strong> and ¼ cup water and stir again to combine. Bring to a simmer and reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring and scraping up any brown bits, until thick and saucy, 10–12 minutes. Remove beef mixture from heat and stir in <strong>1 Tbsp. balsamic vinegar</strong>; season with salt and pepper.</p><h4 class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ InstructionHed-cTDCYA InstructionHedSmall-kvDvLP iwCByY gDeIOw ssMUV">Step 3</h4><p>Spoon beef mixture onto <strong>4 potato rolls</strong>. Serve with <strong>kosher dill spears</strong> and <strong>potato chips</strong> if desired.</p></li></ol></div><div data-testid="TagCloudWrapper" class="TagCloudWrapper-gGgndx kcvoPL Worcestershire sauce, 1 Tbsp. dark brown sugar, and 1 tsp. yellow mustard, then add one 15-oz. can tomato sauce and ¼ cup water and stir again to combine. Sloppy Joes","body":["div",["div",{"className":"container container--body"},["div",{"className":"container--body-inner"},["p","When I was growing up, Manwich, the canned sloppy joe sauce, was a family favorite for making and enjoying quick skillet meals. My still-speedy take uses gochujang for a smoky, spicy undertone. Treat this recipe as a way to hone your ideal levels of heat and sweetness by playing with the amount of gochujang, ketchup, and vinegar. Potato buns provide an ideal soft landing and cold pickle spears are a bright, crunchy counterpoint.
